<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN227-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. avaṉai āṭutuṟaimācāttaṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN227">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>naṉipē taiyē nayaṉil kūṟṟam</l>
<l>virakiṉ maiyiṉ vittaṭ ṭuṇṭaṉai</l>
<l>yiṉṉuṅ kāṇkuvai naṉvā yākuta</l>
<l>loḷiṟuvāṇ maṟavaruṅ kaḷiṟu māvuṅ</l>
<l>kurutiyaṅ kurūuppuṉaṟ porukaḷat toḻiya</l>
<l>nāḷu māṉāṉ kaṭantaṭ ṭeṉṟuniṉ</l>
<l>vāṭupaci yaruttiya paḻitī rāṟṟa</l>
<l>ṉiṉṉō raṉṉa poṉṉiyaṟ perumpūṇ</l>
<l>vaḷava ṉeṉṉum vaṇṭumūcu kaṇṇi</l>
<l>yiṉaiyōṟ koṇṭaṉai yāyi</l>
<l>ṉiṉiyār maṟṟuniṉ pacitīrp pōrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[This is] great folly, loveless Death. (1)</l>
<l>In the absence of fire wood you have cooked [and] eaten the seeds. (2)</l>
<l>Even now you will see [this] become good truth: (3)</l>
<l>him who was there daily, always winning, killing, (6)</l>
<l>while bold men with bright swords, elephant bulls and horses (4)</l>
<l>stayed behind on the battle field in a brilliant flood of blood, (5)</l>
<l>him who is just like you (8ab)</l>
<l>in [his] capacity of ending guilt in order to feed you fading hunger (7)</l>
<l>if you took him (10)</l>
<l>with a bee-swarmed chaplet who is called Vaḷavaṉ, (9)</l>
<l>  with gold-made big ornaments, (8cd)</l>
<l>who else will now end your hunger? (11)   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
